{"type":"message","id":"645cf011","parentId":"381b9456","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:25:30.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me check the most recent log file while it's running.","thinkingSignature":"1f58311088a0421a655ff9d46435fef1dd88fb350c527a24ec59d812d4d1e762"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4gi7rcfy6ie_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 122424.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4gi7rcfy6ie_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"swift-prairie","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":403,"output":117,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12657,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774369524968}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ccdf081","parentId":"645cf011","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:25:30.115Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b4gi7rcfy6ie_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 122424\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. The most recent work is the CFI Analysis with findings about frequency-invariant compression\r\n3. The next pending action is the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n4. Recent pulse was at 2026-03-24 122215\r\n\r\nThe CFI analysis found:\r\n- 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe pending experiment is: \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n\r\nThis is the logical next step. I should:\r\n1. Design an experiment that compares CFI-weighted compression vs frequency-only baseline\r\n2. Implement this in a way that can measure improvement in prediction quality\r\n\r\nLet me think about what this experiment should look like:\r\n\r\nThe core idea is:\r\n- Current: compress by frequency (most common patterns survive)\r\n- New: compress by CFI-weighted score (patterns with high CFI survive even if less frequent)\r\n\r\nThe test would be: take a session, apply both compression methods, then see which one produces better predictions for the next session.\r\n\r\nI'll create a research document that outlines the experiment design. This will be the concrete action.\r\n\r\nLet me create `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` with the experiment design.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression is heavily contaminated by metaprogramming artifacts. A controlled experiment is needed to quantify whether CFI-weighting improves prediction quality over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate CFI-weighted compression experiment design document that specifies methodology, metrics, and implementation plan for comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression approaches.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Status:** Design Phase  \r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Next:** Implementation + Execution\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression in next-pulse prediction because it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) while preserving true causal patterns (CFI>0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Two Compression Methods\r\n1. **Frequency Baseline (FREQ)**\r\n   - Weight = frequency(token)\r\n   - Threshold: keep top N tokens by frequency\r\n   - Current state-of-the-art\r\n\r\n2. **CFI-Weighted (CFI-W)**\r\n   - Weight = CFI(token) × log(frequency(token) + 1)\r\n   - Threshold: keep top N tokens by CFI-weight\r\n   - Filters noise, preserves causal signals\r\n\r\n### Test Protocol\r\n1. Take pulse history: P₁, P₂, ..., Pₙ\r\n2. For each Pᵢ (i from 3 to n-1):\r\n   - Compress P₁..Pᵢ using FREQ → context_F\r\n   - Compress P₁..Pᵢ using CFI-W → context_C\r\n   - Predict Pᵢ₊₁ from each context\r\n   - Compare prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Token overlap:** % of predicted tokens matching actual\r\n- **Semantic coherence:** LLM-judged relevance score (1-5)\r\n- **Causal preservation:** % of high-CFI tokens correctly predicted\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Metric | FREQ | CFI-W | Improvement |\r\n|--------|------|-------|-------------|\r\n| Token overlap | Baseline | +X% | X>0 confirms hypothesis |\r\n| Semantic coherence | Baseline | +Y | Y>0 confirms hypothesis |\r\n| Causal preservation | Z% | ~95% | Z close to 95% confirms filtering |\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n1. Extract token frequencies from pulse history\r\n2. Compute CFI scores (reuse methodology from CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n3. Implement both compression methods\r\n4. Run prediction test across n≥10 pulses\r\n5. Compute metrics and statistical significance\r\n\r\n## Files Needed\r\n- `research/pulse_history_tokens.json` (tokenized pulses)\r\n- `research/cfi_scores.json` (precomputed CFI per token)\r\n- `research/compression_experiment.py` (experiment code)\r\n- `research/experiment_results.md` (output)\r\n, file: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:24:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369530114}}
